2004: On 26 December a severe earthquake on the western coast of the province Aceh in northern Sumatra caused a tsunami that hit 14 countries killing, along the coast of the Indian Ocean, 226,000 people, of which more than half of Aceh.
2005: A series of strong earthquakes hit the western coast of Sumatra between the end of March and the beginning of April.
